The Dar es Salaam Special Zone Police Force are holding Latifa Bakari (33) allegedly murdering her sister’s two-year-old baby at Riverside in Ubungo District in the Tanzania’s commercial city. A statement released by the Dar es Salaam Special Zone Police Commander, ACP Jumanne Muliro on Tuesday claimed that after killing the baby, the suspect stored the body of the deceased in a plastic bucket and threw it in the street. “Her younger sister left her child to her so that she should be taken care of baby … on 5th of April, this year, the suspect committed the murder by beating the baby severely," she added. According to the ACP Muliro, the Police Force was notified by neighbours who discovered the disappearance of the baby and reported the barbaric incident. However, the woman has already been interrogated and confessed to have committed the crime. “The body has been taken to the Muhimbili National Hospital for further examination and the accused will be taken to Court as soon as possible,” he added.